The Pixel class' purpose is to print Pixels on the screen.

Attributes:
- int _x -> the x coordinate of the Pixel. Private.
- int _y -> the y coordinate of the Pixel. Private.
- Uint32 _color -> the color of the Pixel, in integer. Private.

Constructors:
- Pixel(void):
	The default constructor, creates a white Pixel at pos (0;0).
- Pixel(int x, int y, int red, int green, int blue):
	Constructs a Pixel at pos (x;y) and converts the rgb into an integer.
- Pixel(int x, int y, Uint32 color):
	Constructs a Pixel at pos (x;y), with a color integer.
- Pixel(Pixel const &src):
	Constructs a Pixel by copying src.

Member function:
- void draw(SDL_Surface *surface) const:
	Draws itself on the screen 'surface'. Can be done on constant Pixels.

Getters:
- int getX(void) const:
	Returns the x coordinate of the Pixel. Can be done on constant Pixels.
- int getY(void) const:
	Returns the y coordinate of the Pixel. Can be done on constant Pixels.
- int getColor(void) const:
	Returns the color value of the Pixel. Can be done on constant Pixels.

Setters:
- void setX(int x):
	sets the x coordinate of the Pixel to 'x'.
- void setY(int y):
	sets the y coordinate of the Pixel to 'y'.
- void setColor(Uint32 color):
	sets the color of the Pixel to 'color'.
- void setColor(int red, int green, int blue):
	sets the color of the Pixel to rgb converted into an integer.

The = operator has been overloaded, so it is possible to assign Pixels.
